brendan kelly (born 1968) is an irish retired hurler who played as a midfielder for the offaly senior team. kelly joined the team during the 1986-87 national league and was a regular member of the starting fifteen for over a decade. during that time he won one all-ireland winners' medal, three leinster winners' medals and one national hurling league winners' medal. at club level kelly is a one-time county club championship medalist with lusmagh.